In the other manufacturing sectors, the rate of price increase ranged from 0.6 to 9.1 percent.
In the manufacturing industry as a whole, prices increased by 10.2 percent over the past year.
Prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water supply sectors were 18.7 percent higher than a year earlier.
Domestic sales showed the biggest monthly price increase (0.7%) in the sectors producing investment goods in August.
In the consumer goods manufacturing sectors, prices grew by 0.3 percent, while in the energy and downstream industries, prices remained unchanged from the previous month.
Compared to the same month of the previous year, the biggest price increase was observed in August 2008 in the energy and downstream sectors (16.8%).
In the consumer goods sector, the price increased by 6.8 per cent and in the investment goods by 1.4 per cent.
The export sales prices of industry in HUF increased by 1.1 per cent in August compared to the previous month, and decreased by 3.9 per cent in 12-month comparisons.
